3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper introduces higher-order momentum distributions, which could be related to information theory. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new parametrization for deformation that could be useful for machine learning applications. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper develops the mathematical construction of the registration framework with higher-order momenta, which could be relevant to numerical analysis.
